cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper focuses on obtaining 2D and 3D labels for objects on the road, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of interpolation for downstream tasks like tracking and motion planning, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of their annotation tool, which could be of interest to researchers in graphics (cs.GR) who are working on improving annotation tools.
